Requirements for Weather Dashboard Project (C++)
1. Functional Requirements

(What the system should do)

The system should allow the user to enter a city name
The system should fetch weather data for the given city
The system should display:
Temperature
Humidity
Weather condition (rainy, sunny, cloudy, etc.)
The system should handle invalid city names
The system should update and show new data for each request
(Optional) The system can show weather for multiple cities
(Optional) The system can display forecast data
 2. Non-Functional Requirements

(How well the system should work)

The system should respond quickly (within a few seconds)
The system should be user-friendly (simple input/output)
The system should be reliable (handle errors properly)
The system should be portable (run on different systems)
The system should maintain accuracy of weather data
The system should be easy to maintain and update
 3. Hardware Requirements
Computer/Laptop
Minimum 4GB RAM
Internet connection (if using API)
 4. Software Requirements
C++ Compiler (GCC / Turbo C++ / VS Code)
Operating System (Windows / Linux / Mac)
Libraries (if using real data):
libcurl (for API requests)
nlohmann/json (for JSON parsing)
 5. External Requirements (if using API)
Weather API service (e.g., OpenWeatherMap)
API Key for accessing data
